#X obj 89 531 pow~ 1.5;
#X obj 181 797 expr~ copysign(pow(abs($v1) \, $v2) \, $v1);
#X text 37 364 A way to handle this in cases where you can't calculate negative values is to use the absolute function and then copy the sign of the input \, which is possible with ELSE's [sign~] (check its help file).;
#X text 39 788 In [expr~] you can use 'copysign', f 18;
